This summer, wear those shorts. Rock that bikini. Jump in the water and don’t be afraid to try something new. Do it for you. And darling, do it for her. 

Because when you live in your truth, you show other women they can do it too. Without shame. Full of joy. Exactly as you exist right now. 

I’ve been thinking about this a lot lately. 
I’ve started learning to dive. 
And friends have been helping me along the way. 

They’re showing me the moves and working on my belly flops. 
But they’re also cheering. 
Clapping. 
Jumping in themselves. 
Trying their own tricks, 
Making their own mistakes, 

Reminding me that it’s ok to stumble, fall, crash and splash.
Reminding me we can laugh and be happy all the same. 

They’ve inspired me. 
And today, today I hope these words help inspire you
To get out there,
Enjoy summer,
And glow like the amazing sun you are.

You never know who might be encouraged by your light.

x

Video featuring @mariamarlowe and @amandarushforth

#selflove #bodyconfidence #weartheshorts #bodyacceptance

node.text:
How many articles have you seen about BEATING HUNGER?

Crushing those cravings?
Skipping that meal?
 
How many ‘tips’ have you read to ‘end that appetite’?

Like chewing gum. 
Going for a walk. 
Drinking water. 
Painting your nails. 
Taking a nap. 

How many times have you been told not to TRUST YOUR BODY but to IGNORE IT, smother it, starve it? 

Too many, is my guess. 
Too many times. 

And so we learn that hunger queues are bad. But calorie free drinks are good. 
Carbs are evil. But processed diet chemicals are ok. 

We stop tuning in to ourselves, 
Because we are so surrounded by the screams of a 70 billion dollar industry. 

So today, I just want to remind you:
It’s ok to be hungry. 
And it’s ok to eat. 
Our bodies are smart, so so smart. 
And when they need fuel, they’re programmed to say so. 

You deserve to fuel yourself. 

Stop obsessing over shrinking. 
You were born to expand. 

x 

Skit IB @eribodysbeautiful 
Final quote IB @meganroselane 

Workout kit @womensbest @womensbestwear 

#selflove #womensbestathlete #bodyconfidence #dietculture #bodyacceptance

node.text:
Ever wonder how influencers get all those happy candid moments when they’re ALONE? I’ve partnered with @FractureME, my favorite glass photo printing company, to share some fun photo truths. 

But first, a lil’ shoutout to @FractureME, who are the folks behind this idea and all the amazing glass prints here. They’re a carbon-neutral company that makes it really easy to turn memories into elegant wall art. 

Now for the photo truths: 

Lots of influencers use iPhones, tripods and clickers, OR cameras and connected iPhone apps, to take ‘casual, relaxed’ snaps. 

Like for this pic here, I needed the camera to be pretty high, so I balanced a taped up camera on a tripod. I stuck that on a garbage bin. I then put the whole lot onto a suitcase. I used a CLICKER APP connected to my phone to take the pic. Aaaand I took around 30 snaps before I got one where my hand didn’t look a bit wild holding the glass print. 

This sort of stuff happens ALL THE TIME behind the scenes — and that’s OK. 

Today @FractureME and I just want to remind you that all your moments are worthy ones: the unfiltered, the unposed, the curated, the composed. Just make sure you share what makes you feel like you!

Cellulite to PEACHY SELFIE (aka ‘belfie*’) in 10 seconds flat? 

Oooor just another reason to remember the internet is curated and you’re doing great. 

Here’s how I did it:

🍑 Popped my bum on the counter. What’s closest to the mirror/camera looks biggest. It also pulls my skin taunt so hides my CELLULITE. 

🍑 Gave myself a WEDGIE. This creates definition in the bum cheeks so bum looks bigger. 

🍑 Used my hand to hide my SKIN FOLDS. 

🍑 Arched my back, played with angles. 

🍑 Squeezed my back bum cheek. 

🍑 Stopped breathing. 

And BAM there we go. The perfect insta-ready belfie. 

But (or butt?! 😂) here’s the thing: over 80% of women have cellulite. 

Some studies say over 90%. 

It’s super common. Even if we don’t see it on here. Even if it’s so easy to pose, edit, or hide away. 

So remember online isn’t real. 

And you’re amazing.

node.text:
Trust the timing of your life. Because darling, you are creating your own map — and the path, the path is uniquely yours. 

I am so glad that I didn’t find this route, of forever-love and engagement and marriage, in my 20s, 
I wasn’t ready. 
In my heart, in myself, I wasn’t ready. 

I needed time to grow. 

So I worked on loving my body, 
On recovering from years of disordered eating. 
I experienced heartbreak,
I changed jobs. Made new friends. Tripped. Travelled. 

I learned. 

And in my 30s — the magic number women are taught to fear — I started to love myself. 
My heart. My softness. My strength. 

After 32, I became ready to love someone else too.
Then I found him.

So no, no, I don’t regret that my life has unfolded this way. 
Because we each have our own journeys,
Our own paths. 
And our timelines are as varied as the sands tumbling through a clock: 
Unfurling in unique patterns, 
Creating beautiful, infinitely different designs. 

Today, wherever you are in your journey,
I just want to remind you: 

Don’t be ashamed of the steps that brought you here. 
Don’t doubt the routes that come next. 
You are strong enough to drive at your own speed, 
And brave enough to go amazing places. 

You have this. 
Wherever you are, you have this. 
Because you, my dear, are creating your own map. 
And the path is yours. 

x

node.text:
They say you’ll know when it’s the wedding dress for you. 

That it will click:
‘How easy this is.’
‘How perfect this feels.’

I used to laugh, 
When they said that about partners. 

No, I thought. 
That isn’t the way love works. 

But they were right,
And I was wrong,

And now they’re saying that about dresses too. 

I’ve started trying on gowns for the big day,
Ruffles and lace and silk that slinks along the skin. 

The options are overwhelming. 

‘You will know,’ they keep reminding me. 
‘Trust the process. Have fun. Give it time.’

I’m not sure I believe it entirely. 
Fairytales are full of flaws,
And life isn’t like in the movies. 

But I’m open. 
Trying on. Taking off. 
With my head full and my heart happy. 

Willing to listen,
And leaning into love. 

x

Swamp crotch. Camel toe. VPL. Sweat. None of these things are SHAMEFUL. 

But my gosh marketing is trying to CONVINCE US OTHERWISE. 

I saw a campaign the other day that used a lot of these terms here. 
So I pulled clips from THEIR REAL ad. 

And I fixed it for them 🥰. 

Because the body in motion is an INCREDIBLE thing. 

Focusing on HEALTH is WONDERFUL. 

And finding that strength within yourself to pursue your passion — regardless of how your body wobbles or wibbles or jiggles — is the kind of energy I’m here for. 

You’re amazing girl. 
Don’t doubt it. 

x

Kit @womensbest @womensbestwear

Breakups are horrible. You feel like some sliver inside you has snapped, like the pain is too much and too much and you can’t, you can never love again. 

Even if the decision to separate was yours. 
Even if you know you made the right choice. 

When I split from my partner years ago, I felt shattered. 
A shell, shell shocked. 

‘Give it time,’ friends said. 
‘Let yourself heal.’

But what if his love, 
As toxic as it was,
As painful as it was,
What if that love was the kind of love for me? 

What if he was the best I’d ever have? 

We met in Paris months later. 
He was seeing the girl I always worried about. 
‘She’s just a friend, only a friend,’ he’d tell me over her texts.
But weeks after we split she was in his house.
And she was so much more.

By the Eiffel Tower he told me he loved me, 
And he loved her, 
And he didn’t know who to pick. 

I left him there. 

And now, years later, I don’t regret a single thing. 

Because as painful as a separation is, it can still be right.
You might not see it now or today or tomorrow.
But one day you will look back and feel stronger than before. 

You will know that when someone cares for you, you won’t be confused. 
You will realize that when a partnership is healthy, it won’t come with constant barbs of pain. 

You will heal. 

And your heart, your incredible, powerful heart, 
Will learn to love again. 

x
